rlm-wts

Fuzzy-pick a git worktree from the current repository and cd
into it, with Jira annotations on each line.

Lists every worktree via `git worktree list`, then for each
worktree whose branch name contains a Jira-style key (regex
`[A-Z][A-Z0-9]+-[0-9]+`, e.g. DATA-1234, feature/DATA-9)
fetches `(Status) Summary` from Jira via the `acli` CLI in
parallel and shows it inline. The fzf preview pane shows a
fuller multi-line view: key, type, status, summary, assignee.

Display rules:
  * $HOME is shortened to ~
  * the longest common path prefix across all worktrees is
    stripped
  * lines wider than the terminal are truncated from the left,
    preserving the tail, prefixed with "..."

Jira data is cached for 1 hour in ~/.cache/wts-jira/ as
<KEY>.summary and <KEY>.preview. A 3-second watchdog kills any
hung acli call so the picker never freezes. If `acli` is not
installed, the function still works but without annotations.

Aliases: wts
